a form of asbestos once use to make kent cigarette filter have cause a high percentage of cancer death among a group of worker expose to it more than 30 year ago , researcher report .
the asbestos fiber , crocidolite , be unusually resilient once it enter the lung , with even brief exposure to it cause symptom that show up decade later , researcher say .
lorillard inc. , the unit of new york - based loews corp. that make kent cigarette , stop use crocidolite in its micronite cigarette filter in 1956 .
although preliminary finding be report more than a year ago , the latest result appear in today 's new england journal of medicine , a forum likely to bring new attention to the problem .
a lorillard spokewoman say , `` this be an old story .
we 're talk about year ago before anyone hear of asbestos have any questionable property .
there be no asbestos in our product now . ''
neither lorillard nor the researcher who study the worker be aware of any research on smoker of the kent cigarette .
`` we have no useful information on whether user be at risk , '' say james a. talcott of boston 's dana - farber cancer institute .
dr. talcott lead a team of researcher from the national cancer institute and the medical school of harvard university and boston university .
the lorillard spokeswoman say asbestos be use in `` very modest amount '' in make paper for the filter in the early 1950 s and replace with a different type of filter in 1956 .
from 1953 to 1955 , 9.8 billion kent cigarette with the filter be sell , the company say .
among 33 men who work closely with the substance , 28 have die -- more than three time the expect number .
four of the five survive worker have asbestos - related disease , include three with recently diagnose cancer .
the total of 18 death from malignant mesothelioma , lung cancer and asbestosis be far higher than expect , the researcher say .
`` the morbidity rate be a striking find among those of us who study asbestos - related disease , '' say dr. talcott .
the percentage of lung cancer death among the worker at the west groton , mass. , paper factory appear to be the highest for any asbestos worker study in western industrialize country , he say .
the plant , which be own by hollingsworth & vose co. , be under contract with lorillard to make the cigarette filter .
the find probably will support those who argue that the u.s. should regulate the class of asbestos include crocidolite more stringently than the common kind of asbestos , chrysotile , find in most school and other building , dr. talcott say .
the u.s. be one of the few industrialized nation that do n't have a higher standard of regulation for the smooth , needle - like fibers such as crocidolite that be classify as amphobiles , accord to brooke t. mossman , a professor of pathlogy at the university of vermont college of medicine .
more common chrysotile fibers be curly and be more easily reject by the body , dr. mossman explain .
in july , the environmental protection agency impose a gradual ban on virtually all use of asbestos .
by 1997 , almost all remain use of cancer - cause asbestos will be outlaw .
about 160 worker at a factory that make paper for the kent filter be expose to asbestos in the 1950 s .
area of the factory be particularly dusty where the crocidolite be use .
worker dump large burlap sack of the import material into a huge bin , pour in cotton and acetate fibers and mechanically mix the dry fibers in a process use to make filter .
worker describe `` cloud of blue dust '' that hung over part of the factory , even though exhaust fan ventilate the area .
`` there 's no question that some of those worker and manager contract asbestos - related disease , '' say darrell phillips , vice president of human resource for hollingsworth & vose .
`` but you have to recognize that these event take place 35 year ago .
it have no bear on our work force today .
yield on money - market mutual fund continue to slide , amid sign that portfolio manager expect further decline in interest rate .
the average seven - day compound yield of the 400 taxable fund track by ibc 's money fund report ease a fraction of a percentage point to 8.45 % from 8.47 % for the week end tuesday .
compound yield assume reinvestment of dividend and that the current yield continue for a year .
average maturity of the fund ' investment lengthen by a day to 41 day , the longest since early august , accord to donoghue 's .
long maturities be think to indicate decline interest rate because they permit portfolio manager to retain relatively higher rate for a longer period .
short maturities be consider a sign of rise rate because portfolio manager can capture higher rate sooner .
the average maturity for fund open only to institution , consider by some to be a stronger indicator because those manager watch the market closely , reach a high point for the year -- 33 day .
nevertheless , say brenda malizia negus , editor of money fund report , yield `` may blip up again before they blip down '' because of recent rise in short - term interest rate .
the yield on six - month treasury bill sell at monday 's auction , for example , rise to 8.04 % from 7.90 % .
despite recent decline in yield , investor continue to pour cash into money fund .
asset of the 400 taxable fund grow by $ 1.5 billion during the latest week , to $ 352.7 billion .
typically , money - fund yield beat comparable short - term investment because portfolio manager can vary maturities and go after the highest rate .
the top money fund be currently yield well over 9 % .
dreyfus world - wide dollar , the top - yield fund , have a seven - day compound yield of 9.37 % during the latest week , down from 9.45 % a week earlier .
it invest heavily in dollar - denominate security overseas and be currently waive management fee , which boost its yield .
the average seven - day simple yield of the 400 fund be 8.12 % , down from 8.14 % .
the 30 - day simple yield fall to an average 8.19 % from 8.22 % ; the 30 - day compound yield slide to an average 8.53 % from 8.56 % .
