estonia ( ee ) ; latvia ( lv ) ; lithuania ( lt ) ; germany ( de ): italy ( it ) ; spain ( es ) ; slovakia ( sk ) ; unite state ( us )
international ; government ; telecom ; technology ; science
nato consider cyber attack a threat to military and civilian computer network after the estonian government be struck by cyber attack in 2007 .
nato ally have sign an agreement to fund a research center to bolster defenses against cyber attack .
on 14 may 2008 7 nato ally sign an agreement to fund a research center .
the center will bolster nato 's defenses against cyber attack .
the center will be operational in august 2008 .
the center will formally open in 2009 .
a staff of 30 specialist will conduct research and train on cyber warfare .
nato consider cyber attack a grow threat to military and civilian computer network .
the research center be based in tallinn , estonia .
defense chief from estonia , latvia , lithuania , germany , italy , spain and slovakia sign the agreement .
the agreement will provide staff and fund for the research center .
in 2007 the estonian government be struck by cyber attack .
the cyber attack cripple government and corporate computer network .
the cyber attack be unprecedented .
the cyber attack follow a dispute over the relocation of a soviet war memorial in estonia 's capital .
many suspect the kremlin of the cyber attack .
russia deny involvement with the cyber attack .
nato 's top commander in charge of military modernization u.s. gen. james mattis state --
nato will cooperate to bring together the best mind together in cyber defense .
nato cannot say that nato will not defend the web that everybody need .
the u.s. will join the project as an observer .
other nato nation may join the project later .
at a news conference at the research center estonian defense minister jaak aaviksoo state that --
cyber space essentially have no border .
it be difficult to defend the sovereignty of land and sea border and air space .
it be even more complicated in borderless cyber space where there be no smoke gun , fingerprint or footprint .
the agreement be sign during a regular meet of chief of defense staff from the 26 nato ally .
estonia be a baltic nation .
