afghanistan ( af )
narcotic ; international
a u.n. representative state that the conversion of opium resin into heroin be increasingly be done inside afghanistan but that the chemical need to complete the conversion be be smuggle into afghanistan from other country .
the u.n. representative request the international community share more information on know smuggler of the chemical .
the u.n. state on 28 july 2008 that the international community should do more to stop chemical use to convert opium to heroin from reach afghanistan and detail increase sophistication in afghanistan 's drug trade .
afghanistan produce more than 90 percent of the world 's opium .
opium production in afghanistan have increase since the u.s. @-@ lead invasion remove the taliban regime in 2001 .
official in the american @-@ back government and taliban militant be believe to profit from the illicit trade .
u.n. figure show afghanistan yield approximately 9000 ton of opium in 2007 which could create more than 900 ton of heroin .
afghanistan 's representative for the u.n. office on drug and crime christina oguz state the conversion of opium resin into heroin be increasingly be done inside afghanistan mostly at laboratory in the border region in the insurgency @-@ plague south and the east .
oguz state to reporter in kabul that evidence of higher quality afghan heroin indicate that the people run the lab be get assistance from chemist who have come from outside the country as foreign consultant .
oguz state the chemist originate from country near the border but do not detail specific country .
oguz state the chemical need to make the heroin be be smuggle from china , south korea , european country , include russia , and other part of the world .
oguz state the so @-@ call precursor chemical such as acetic anhydride also have legal use include in the paint and pharmaceutical industry .
oguz state the chemical often be legally export but later divert to afghanistan for illicit goal and afghanistan have no major legal industry that would require such chemical .
oguz state --
blame afghanistan alone for the heroin problem in the world be not correct .
afghanistan do produce the opium which be the raw material for heroin but it be not possible to make heroin without certain chemical that be not produce inside afghanistan and be smuggle into afghanistan .
more than 200 ton of the chemical have be seize by afghan authority since 2006 but some 13000 ton be need based on 2007 's opium production figure .
the figure suggest the confiscate amount represent a small fraction of the total smuggle in .
most seizure of the chemical occur along the eastern border with pakistan but a good deal come via the western border with iran .
oguz state the international community should share more information on know smuggler of the chemical who be long @-@ establish and based in afghanistan 's neighboring country .
western official be increasingly concern that taliban militant be bankrolling the insurgency through the drug trade .
the u.n. brief come in the wake of allegation that afghan president hamid karzai protect drug lord for political reason .
a former senior u.s. state department counter @-@ narcotic official write in an article in the 27 july 2008 issue of new york time magazine that narco @-@ corruption go to the top of the afghan government .
the official alleged karzai be reluctant to move against big drug lord in karzai 's political power base in the south of afghanistan where most opium be produce .
karzai have state commitment to eliminate corruption and battle the drug trade .
oguz state on 28 july 2008 that corruption exist within the system but afghanistan lack a well @-@ train police force for many year and official be only now take step in fight corruption .
