the the ministry of economic affair ( moea ) approve lingsen precision industry , king yuan electronics , ic assembly company sigurd corp. and siliconware precision industry for chinese investment .
on 8 april 2008 the ministry of economic affair ( moea ) announce approval for 4 chinese investment proposal from chinese manufacturer .
lingsen precision industry , king yuan electronics , ic assembly company sigurd corp. and siliconware precision industry be approve for investment and will invest in integrate circuit package ( icp ) and test .
the company will invest 10 million us dollar , 20 million us dollar , 6.7 million us dollar , and 50 million us dollar respectively .
the proposal have a total investment amount of 86.7 million us dollar ( 2.64 billion nt dollar ) .
the moea determine in a meet on 8 april 2008 that the investment proposal meet the clause in the china investment procedure issue by the ministry 's investment commission .
the investment commission 's executive secretary fan liang @-@ tung state the investment procedure aim to ensure taiwan 's investment in china will not harm taiwan 's industry and economy such as by leak key technology to the mainland .
under the procedure investment plan require approval from the moea if the plan involve a single investment that exceed 100 million us dollar , the company 's total investment in china reach 200 million us dollar , or the investment could transfer core local industry ' technology to china .
fan state core industry mainly involve the manufacture of 8 @-@ inch wafer and 4 @-@ inch tft panel as well as ic package .
after the meet on 8 april 2008 the commission require write document to further assess the plan which contain each company 's commitment on the term of investment include the financial plan , information on any technology transfer and the company 's domestic investment as well as employment information .
fan state the commission be primarily concern with the term of future investment in taiwan .
fan state lingsen precision industry , king yuan electronics , ic assembly company sigurd corp. and siliconware precision industry have make commitment to return capital to taiwan in the amount of 2 billion nt dollar , 19.2 billion nt dollar , 3 billion nt dollar and 23 billion nt dollar respectively by 2011 .
fan state the commission will ensure the commitment be uphold once the investment be under way .
fan state the procedure would push chinese investment from taiwan to focus on down scale manufacturer rather than technology @-@ concentrate maker in a bid to keep high @-@ end technology in taiwan .
fan state the commission will hold a 2 nd round of meeting to decide if the proposal will take effect and that the final decision will be make by 30 april 2008 .
