1999 @-@ 06 @-@ 30
india ( in ) ; korea , democratic people 's republic of ( kp )
international ; technology ; weapon ; government
indian official seize missile assembly line from the north korean vessel the kuwolsan on 30 june 1999 .
the discovery heighten suspicion of north korean weapon proliferation .
on 30 june 1999 indian custom agent in the northwestern port city of kandla board the north korean freighter kuwolsan .
follow a melee with the crew of the kuwolsan , custom agent discover an assembly line for ballistic missile .
u.s. intelligence official state libyan government be the intend recipient of the cargo .
the kuwolsan depart north korea 's nampo harbor on 10 april 1999 .
record show that on 20 april 1999 the kuwolsan make detour to 2 thai port to pick up 14000 ton of sugar for resale along the way to the kuwolsan 's destination .
the kuwolsan switch course in order to sell the sugar to an indian company after a deal to sell the sugar to algerians fail .
an indian investigator state that the crew of the kuwolsan should not have pick up extra cargo at several port when carry 200 ton of sensitive equipment and that such activity be crazy .
indian custom official be tip off to possible contraband on the kuwolsan while the kuwolsan be en route to kandla .
the kuwolsan be rumored to be carry arm or ammunition possibly intend for pakistan .
indian port official be wait when the kuwolsan arrive in kandla on 25 june 1999 .
irregularity in the kuwolsan 's paper be apparent within the first few hour of investigation .
indian official learn that the company in malta list as the intend recipient of the cargo be fictitious .
indian official question why anyone in malta would choose to buy water refine equipment from north korea when malta be a short flight from europe .
indian custom agent question the captain of the kuwolsan tae min hun .
tae block every request and threaten international reprisal if indian official do not allow tae to leave kandla .
on 30 june 1999 custom official demand to search the kuwolsan 's cargo box and tae state that the kuwolsan have receive a telex from north korean official .
tae receive instruction from official in pyongyang to allow no one to open the cargo box at all cost .
the official indian after @-@ action report state tae would not open any more box as per the telex .
the report state the crew member shout at and abuse the custom officer .
accord to witness account and video footage of the encounter , tae and the crew of the kuwolsan barricade the door of the kuwolsan with the crew ' body .
an indian official who be present on the kuwolsan and who spoke on the condition of anonymity state the situation become physical and there be fisticuffs .
the official state the crew begin close the hatch to the cargo hold with the custom inspector still inside .
on 1 july 1999 arm troop and a group of government weapon expert aid custom official and gain forcible entry onto the kuwolsan .
a few crate among the kuwolsan 's cargo contain equipment that could be use in a water treatment plant .
inspector find pump , nozzle and a few valve .
the cargo box be labeled as water refinement equipment .
document from the investigation contain a partial list of the content of most of the cargo crate which include --
component for missile subassembly .
machine tool for set up a fabrication facility .
instrumentation for evaluate the performance of a full missile system .
equipment for calibrate missile component .
rocket nose cone , stack of metal pipe and heavy @-@ duty press use for mill high @-@ grade steel .
a plate @-@ bend machine capable of roll thick metal sheet , toroidal air bottle use to guide warhead after separation from a missile , and theodolite that measure missile trajectory .
several box of engineer drawing , blueprint , notebook , textbook and report .
personal item presumably intend for north korean worker , include cookbook in korean , korean spice , pickle and acupuncture set .
an indian government official familiar with the kuwolsan discovery state that in the past official have see missile or engine part , but here be an entire assembly line for missile offer for sale .
the official state that this be a complete technology transfer .
a technical committee of indian missile expert state that the equipment be unimpeachable and irrefutable evidence of a plan to transfer not just missile but missile @-@ make capability .
the technical panel write in a report that the cargo point to only one end @-@ use , namely the assemble of missile and manufacture of the part and subassemblies of surface to surface missile .
investigator search the blueprint that be keep inside number plastic jacket and wrap in brown paper .
some of the packet be labeled in english as scud b or scud c. nearly all of the drawing show rocket or section of rocket with note and mathematical formula handwritten in korean .
native korean speaker assist in translation but the document contain technical code invent by north korean scientist to replace scientific term in russian or chinese .
the investigation ultimately yield information about north korea 's weapon program which indian authority share with ally government .
the scud b and scud c design find on the kuwolsan be from older north korean missile programs which be derived from soviet missile design of the 1950 s .
one indian government official who study the blueprint state the science be old and date but still functional .
retire director of the state department 's office on strategic , proliferation and military issue in the bureau of intelligence and research greg thielmann state the cia utilize the blueprint to make full mock @-@ up of missile complete with decals .
the blueprint include information pertaining to the inner working of north korea 's missile industry which have be the focus of contention between the unite state and north korea since the 1980 s .
the cargo on the kuwolsan do not include everything need for missile production which raise the possibility that there may have be earlier and possible later shipment .
missile expert and senior analyst at the center for nonproliferation study timothy v. mccarthy examine some of the blueprint and other evidence and state this be a slice in time of a technology transfer from north korea to libya .
mccarthy state the intelligence find help u.s. official learn how north korean missile scientist learn .
mccarthy state the information give u.s. official an idea of how capable north korean scientist be of progress to more advanced missile and give u.s. official insight into the aspect of proliferation when one country 's official attempt to transfer technology to another country 's official .
mccarthy state no one can stop libyan scientist once the scientist be capable of make missile .
the kuwolsan and the crew be unaccounted for after indian official release the kuwolsan in 2000 .
ship expert at lloyd 's maritime division in london state the kuwolsan 's name be change in the summer of 2000 to sun grisan 9 .
as of the week of 3 august 2003 the sun grisan 9 be still in service and be last report headed to the somalian capital of mogadishu .
the nature of the sun grisan 9 's cargo be unknown .
as of 14 august 2003 the evidence from the kuwolsan be secure in a military warehouse in new delhi .
as state in court document and interview with official in the unite state and india the kuwolsan incident have reinforce a view of north korea as the world 's most dangerous source of weapon proliferation .
in 1999 north korean leader kim jong il expel u.n. inspector , abandon the nuclear non @-@ proliferation treaty and declare plan to build an atomic weapon .
u.s. intelligence official state that north korean official be continue global trade in technology for weapon of mass destruction include instruction for make advanced missile .
successive u.s. administration have condemn north korea 's missile sale to such country as iran and syria .
on 31 august 1998 north korean official launch a 3 @-@ stage missile which heighten fear of advanced north korean design capable of reach the u.s. mainland .
the first stage splash down in the sea of japan , the second stage cross the main island of japan and the third broke up and traveled 3450 mile downrange and fall into the pacific ocean .
the missile test fueled work on a u.s. missile defense shield .
north korean official have defend the right to sell weapon and have state that north korean official be not bound by international treaty restrict such trade .
north korean official have sell missile and part to yemen which receive 15 scud missile after the missile be briefly intercept by u.s. and spanish naval crew off the yemeni coast in december 1998 .
libya appear to be the latest beneficiary of north korean weapon .
other nation include iran , pakistan and syria be know to have receive similar help .
the kuwolsan cargo attest to the existence of a gray zone compose of a combination of weak state , open border , lack of control and a market of buyer and seller of weapon of mass destruction .
small package be sometimes deliver in the luggage of individual airline passenger such as a taiwanese businessman arrest at zurich 's airport in 2000 with north korean missile part in a rucksack .
large item be move in freighter such as the kuwolsan while technical information and design be accessible via the internet .
korea specialist with the center for nonproliferation study at the monterey institute of international study in california daniel pinkston state that intercept weapon and equipment be difficult but not impossible but that human exchange of plan , data , and intellectual property be difficult to intercept .
